 Broken glass, plastic bottles, foam packaging from under household appliances —this garbage is in the 
area of SU-5 on the Bypass street of the city of Almetyevsk ( coordinates (#geo-tagging) -
https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/edit?mid=1EFEGhz7EFRWauUOq7PbfMHYwPDusvXIB&ll=54.897998612017034%2C52.30864801843275&z=12 ) has become a real headache for us. The road is only 
840 meters. Its roadsides are regularly littered with garbage. Previously, there were garbage cans, now 
they have been removed. And people continue to throw out of habit. I believe that garbage is in the 
minds of people who are used to throwing waste on the side of the road. I love my city, and I, as a 
resident of Almetyevsk, resent the irresponsible attitude towards it. We were all taught from childhood 
to clean up after ourselves and not to throw out garbage anywhere.
I was among three dozen employees, despite the bad weather, who went out on April 24 to clean up the 
territory. Two backhoe loaders, a large excavator and three dump trucks were used at full capacity. We 
have removed 14 trucks of garbage from a small area.

Hi guys, I am impressed by all your cleaning up activities. I'd like to thank you for all your inspiration.  I would like to share my experience of cleaning up the community. Luckily, I can enjoy the view of the park from my office window. Sometimes people have party or event at the park. They always take their belongings and garbage when they leave. However, this Monday, when I had lunch at the park I spot a area with lots of garbage lying on the ground. I think someone must have a party at the weekend. I pick up some food container and package and throw them away. Then I remember that I should document the" crime scene" and send the pictures to the local council and share with ECO. I found some bags from my office and started picking up all the garbage. After collecting all the garbage and threw them into the public garbage container,  I took all the bottles to the local recycle centre. Doing a small good thing for the community makes me feel fulfilled.
